summary:
**Reporting and Review:**

* The Commission will submit an annual report to the General Assembly (para 15)

**Roles and Responsibilities:**

* The Commission's main purpose is to provide advice to the Security Council in post-conflict situations (para 16)
* The Commission's advice will be relevant to the Economic and Social Council for sustained attention to countries in transition (para 17)

**Decision-Making:**

* The Commission will act on the basis of consensus among its members (para 18)

**Working Methods:**

* The Commission will adopt flexible working methods, including videoconferencing and meetings outside New York (para 19)
The Security Council:

20. Calls on the Commission to integrate a gender perspective into all its work;

21. Encourages the Commission to consult with civil society, non-governmental organizations, including women's organizations, and the private sector;

22. Recommends that the Commission terminate its consideration of a country-specific situation when foundations for sustainable peace and development are established or upon request by national authorities;

23. Requests the Secretary-General to establish a small peacebuilding support office to assist and support the Commission;

24. Requests the Secretary-General to establish a multi-year standing peacebuilding fund for post-conflict peacebuilding;

25. Requests the Secretary-General to report to the General Assembly on the arrangements for establishing the peacebuilding fund;

26. Calls on relevant bodies and Member States to communicate the names of members of the Organizational Committee to the Secretary-General;

27. Decides that the arrangements will be reviewed five years after adoption to ensure they are appropriate to fulfil the Commission's functions;

28. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
